White Community Kneel Before Black Community To Seek For Forgiveness For Years Of Racism A video shared online shows the moment White people went on their knees to beg Black people for forgiveness for all the years of racism they have suffered. Houstonians gathered Sunday, May 31, at Cuney Homes in the Third Ward to pray for the family of George Floyd following his murder. During the prayer, the White people in attendance knelt down and asked for forgiveness for years of racism. The Black community accepted the apology and joined them in prayer. Watch The Heartwarming Video Below; White community kneel before members of the Black community to beg for forgiveness for years of #racism A post shared by  Lindaikejiblog (@lindaikejiblogofficial) on Jun 1, 2020 at 5:29am PDT  White Community Kneel Before Black Community To Seek For Forgiveness For Years Of Racism A video shared online shows the moment White people went on their knees to beg Black people for forgiveness for all the years of racism they have suffered. Houstonians gathered Sunday, May 31, at Cuney Homes… June 1, 2020 In "Foreign" Mark Zuckerberg has revealed plans to use his platform to combat racial injustice as he spoke about racism and police brutality. The Facebook founder made this known as he mourned the murder of, not just George Floyd, but also Breonna Taylor, Ahmaud Arbery and others. Mark Zuckerberg reacted to the… June 1, 2020 In "Foreign" By Wendell Roelf CAPE TOWN - South Africa's University of Cape Town removed a statue of British imperialist Cecil Rhodes on Thursday to cheers from students, a symbolic move that exposes persistent racial divides two decades after the end of apartheid. The statue at the university, one of Africa's top… April 10, 2015 In "Foreign"